description: In Seattle, the team hunts down a bizarre killer who carves roman numerals into his victims' mouths; Garcia attends an execution.

title: A Thousand Suns
description: When a commercial jet full of passengers crashes in a Colorado field, the team discovers that the plane was brought down by remote control.

title: The Itch
description: The team probes the death of an investigative journalist who walked into oncoming traffic and had mysterious scars and scratches on his body.

title: Boxed In
description: The team goes to San Diego to investigate the sudden reappearance of a boy who vanished on Halloween one year earlier and was held captive in a box.

title: If the Shoe Fits
description: The team goes to Montana, where three young men are found dead with cell phones stuffed in their mouths with the alarms set to go off at midnight.

title: Hashtag
description: The team looks into the murder of a teen whose corpse appears in a selfie on social media sites; Morgan struggles to find private time with Savannah.

title: The Boys of Sudworth Place
description: When a defense attorney known for working with troubled youth is abducted, the team wonders if the disappearance is linked to one of his cases.

title: Fate
description: The team is called to Virginia, where victims are being brutally stabbed, then neatly displayed in fresh clothes; Rossi receives a surprising visitor.

title: Amelia Porter
description: In Salt Lake City, the team investigates a triple homicide that puts them on the trail of a fugitive who disappeared after committing a grisly crime.

title: The Forever People
description: In Boulder City, Nevada, the team looks for a serial killer amidst a cult that freezes members as part of their induction ritual.

title: Anonymous
description: When a string of seemingly unrelated murders occurs in Tallahassee, the team learns the victims were all organ donors; Rossi loses a close friend.

title: Nelson's Sparrow
description: A case hits home for Rossi when a colleague from his past is found murdered, setting him on the trail of a bird-obsessed serial killer.

title: Hero Worship
description: When an Indianapolis coffee shop explodes and the media rallies around a local hero, the team's seemingly open-and-shut case could go up in smoke.

title: Scream
description: The team is called in to investigate the deaths of two California women found in dumpsters with their bodies beaten and throats slashed.

title: Lockdown
description: The warden of a maximum security prison calls on the team when two guards are murdered, but more danger looms when the trouble escalates into a riot.

title: Breath Play
description: In Wisconsin, the team hunts for a serial killer whose victims are obsessed with a best-selling erotic novel; Kate suspects her niece has a secret.

title: Rock Creek Park
description: When the wife of a junior congressman is abducted, the unit discovers that the motives behind the crime are not what the FBI suspects.

title: Beyond Borders
description: When a family on vacation in the Caribbean is abducted, the team is called upon to assist Special Agent Jack Garrett and his team in Barbados.

title: A Place at the Table
description: The team investigates the murder of a family found dead at their dining room table; Hotch helps Jessica keep Roy out of a nursing home.

title: Mr. Scratch
description: The unit searches for a criminal who puts his victims into a violent hallucinogenic state, causing them to kill their loved ones.

title: Protection
description: The team takes the case of a delusional killer who believes he is punishing criminals; Kate's niece sneaks out at night with a stranger.

title: The Hunt
description: When Kate's niece and her friend are kidnapped, the team rushes to find them before they become victims of traffickers.

title: The Job
description: As the BAU searches for a serial killer who paints his victims' faces, prospective new team member Tara Lewis gets a chance to show off her skills.

title: The Witness
description: A poison gas attack on a commuter bus brings the team to L.A., where they zero in on a businessman who was late to work and is acting strangely.

title: 'Til Death Do Us Part
description: The murder of two brides-to-be in Savannah, Georgia, leaves the team looking for a jilted lover. But a third body forces them to rethink the profile.

title: Outlaw
description: When three teens are found slain in a New Mexico restaurant, the team sees uncanny similarities to a cold case from six years ago.

title: The Night Watch
description: An elaborate murder scene triggers a search for a street artist whose identity is a well-kept secret. Work takes a toll on Lewis's home life.

title: Pariahville
description: A killing in a town populated by sex offenders presents a daunting challenge for the team. Meanwhile, Lewis receives a tempting job offer.

title: Target Rich
description: As the team celebrates JJ's return, Rossi's daughter begs for help finding a missing college student. An interview with Montolo takes a dramatic turn.

title: Awake
description: The BAU races to track down a man who's abducting and torturing victims along a Phoenix highway. A threat forces Garcia to bunk down at the office.

title: Internal Affairs
description: After an attack on undercover DEA agents in Texas, the NSA calls in Hotch's team to investigate an online drug cartel and root out an agency mole.

title: Future Perfect
description: Two bodies found with strange markings in Florida spur a hunt for a suspect with medical knowledge and a morbid fixation.

title: Entropy
description: As the team closes in on the network of hitmen threatening Garcia, Reid becomes locked in a high-stakes showdown with a woman known as "Miss .45."

title: Drive
description: The BAU traces a series of headless bodies in Boston to a ride-sharing service. But there's something more that the victims have in common.

title: The Bond
description: While the team struggles to connect the dots between several truck stop killings, a troubled man reconnects with his long-lost biological mother.

title: Hostage
description: After an 18-year-old escapes from a basement where she's been held captive for years, the race is on to find her tormentor and his other victims.

title: A Badge and a Gun
description: Adding up clues from several suffocations in L.A., the team begins to fear the killer is a rogue FBI agent. A text from Savannah puts Morgan on edge.

title: Derek
description: To survive an agonizing ordeal, Morgan slips into a trance, where he connects with his late father and realizes what Savannah wanted to tell him.

title: The Sandman
description: The BAU welcomes Morgan back after a six-month leave, but the celebration is cut short by news of a ritualistic family murder in Kansas.

title: A Beautiful Disaster
description: On a quest to find out who targeted Morgan and Savannah, the team uncovers links to a past case. A note from the sniper leads to a harrowing showdown.

title: Tribute
description: Emily Prentiss reunites with the BAU to track down a murderer who's mimicking crimes by famous serial killers like Jack the Ripper and Son of Sam.

title: Inner Beauty
description: The team tries to figure out what drives a killer to disfigure his female victims' faces. Rossi reconnects with someone from his past.

title: Devil's Backbone
description: A notorious female serial killer draws the members of the BAU into a twisted mind game when they ask her for help finding two missing boys.

title: The Storm
description: When Hotch is arrested in a SWAT raid, the team scrambles to clear his name, but they soon realize it's part of a larger plot that's unfolding fast.

title: The Crimson King
description: A new agent, Luke Alvez, joins the team to help them catch the Crimson King, one of the escaped killers from last season.

title: Sick Day
description: Fresh from the tragic aftermath of a child abduction case, a vulnerable JJ returns home to find that her youngest child is sick.

title: Taboo
description: The gruesome murder of three single mothers leads to an investigation of what they had in common and why they were killed.

title: Keeper
description: The body parts of several people who had gone missing over a period of six months are discovered in a homeless man's shopping cart.

title: The Anti-Terrorism Squad
description: A 17-year-old girl returns home, well past her curfew, to run into the dead bodies of her family members, who have been shot execution-style.

title: Elliott's Pond
description: The team is called in to investigate after three children go missing in the same area where two children disappeared 30 years ago.

title: Mirror Image
description: The team launches an investigation into the sudden arrival of a mysterious man claiming to be Tara's younger brother, Gabriel.

title: Scarecrow
description: The team heads to Yakima, Washington, after a local girl goes missing and the remains of several people are found along a creek bed.

title: Profiling 202
description: A familiar voice from the past calls Rossi on his birthday to inform him that he has abducted a woman, and he has more information to share.

title: Seek & Destroy
description: The team investigates a series of brutal, destructive home invasions that end in murder in upscale San Diego neighborhoods.

title: Surface Tension
description: While dissecting a corpse in an anatomy class, a teacher and her students discover a strange mark that was found on another dead body.

title: A Good Husband
description: The discoveries of two male torsos within close proximity of each other in Palm Springs appear to point to a single killer.

title: Spencer
description: Spencer is arrested near the U.S.-Mexico border, after a stash of heroin is discovered in the trunk of the vehicle that he's driving.

title: Collision Course
description: Two pedestrians are run down on the same road by two similar vehicles, leading the team to wonder if the incidents point to a pattern.

title: Alpha Male
description: With Spencer's incarceration at the back of their minds, the BAU heads to Philadelphia to investigate a series of acid attacks.

title: Assistance is Futile
description: A number of corpses are found in New York City, victims of a serial killer with an evident fondness for breaking bones.

title: In the Dark
description: A series of home invasion stabbings and shootings of hunters in Vermont have the team wondering if they are dealing with two killers.

title: Hell's Kitchen
description: A girl's disappearance in New York City just before her 16th birthday appears to have similarities to two previous abduction killings.

title: True North
description: The dead bodies of three victims are discovered tied to stakes in the Arizona desert, and in varying stages of decomposition.

title: Unforgettable
description: Stephen's friend from the BAP is hospitalized following what looks like a heart attack but it turns out to be something more.

title: Green Light
description: The victim of one of the team's former cases turns up, posing as a nurse to Spencer's mother, shortly before the latter disappears.

title: Red Light
description: Reid finds himself returning to prison for an unusual tte--tte with the accomplice of the girl who abducted his mother.
